						<summary>

						<p>Broken slab built into the wall of Police-Patel-chāvaḍi.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Bhuvanaikamalla [Sōmēśvara II] 1076-77 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The left half of the slab is broken and lost. It states that the queen (name lost) of Chālukya Bhuvanaikamalla made a grant of land for the worship and offerings to the god, maintenance and repairs (of the temple) and for feeding ascetics in the temple of god Svayaṁbhu Mūlasthānadēva. The administrative division Eḍadoṟe-nāḍu is mentioned here.</p>						

						<p>In the date portion only śaka 998 Naḷa. (A)māvāsye, Friday is available. It may correspond with 1076-77 A.D. [In the month Āśvīja, Amāvāsye occured on a Friday corresponding to September 30].</p>						

						</summary>
